\begin{flushleft}
Fix now $\tau$ $\in$ R and X $\in$ g. Then, if m$\tau$ denotes the multiplication by $\tau$ in R, the
\end{flushleft}


\begin{flushleft}
map $\eta$(t) = $\xi$X ($\tau$ t) = $\xi$X ◦ m$\tau$ (t) is again a homomorphism from R into G and since
