\end{flushleft}


\begin{flushleft}
Lie algebra g, we shall denote by gl(g) the Lie algebra of all endomorphisms of g with
\end{flushleft}


\begin{flushleft}
the commutator as bracket and by GL(g) the group of all non singular endomorphisms
\end{flushleft}


\begin{flushleft}
of g as a vector space. Hence gl(g) is the Lie algebra of GL(g). The map X $\rightarrow$ ad X
\end{flushleft}


\begin{flushleft}
is a Lie algebra homomorphism whose image is a Lie subalgebra of gl(g) denoted ad g.
\end{flushleft}


\begin{flushleft}
