\begin{flushleft}
It is actually possible to give an explicit description of the automorphisms of Hd . It
\end{flushleft}


\begin{flushleft}
is immediate to see that each of the following families of maps are automorphisms:
\end{flushleft}


\begin{flushleft}
(i) Symplectic maps: For any X $\in$ Sp(d, R), (
\end{flushleft}





\begin{flushleft}
q
\end{flushleft}


\begin{flushleft}
